<p>When hosting multiple sites using a single installation of mojoPortal, the first site is considered the root site and all other sites are considered child sites.</p>
<p>The root site can specify which Features and Web Parts are available to the child sites.</p>
<p>Select items from the &quot;All Features&quot; or &quot;All Web Parts&quot; list by clicking them, then use the button with the -&gt; to add features to the child site.</p>
<p>Features can be removed by selecting items from the &quot;Selected Features&quot; or &quot;Selected WebParts&quot; lists and using the &lt;- button to remove them.</p>
